0:12:07.783,000 --> 0:12:12,000
So a firefly vampire,

260
0:12:13.628,000 --> 0:12:17,000
brought to you by natural selection.

261
0:12:17.98,000 --> 0:12:2,000
We still have a lot to learn about fireflies,

262
0:12:21.161,000 --> 0:12:24,000
but it looks like many stories will remain untold,

263
0:12:24.544,000 --> 0:12:26,000
because around the world, firefly populations

264
0:12:26.973,000 --> 0:12:28,000
are blinking out.

265
0:12:29.628,000 --> 0:12:31,000
The main culprit: habitat loss.

266
0:12:32.216,000 --> 0:12:34,000
Pretty much everywhere, the fields and forests,

267
0:12:34.702,000 --> 0:12:36,000
the mangroves and meadows that fireflies need to survive,

268
0:12:37.649,000 --> 0:12:4,000
are giving way to development and to sprawl.

269
0:12:41.281,000 --> 0:12:45,000
Here's another problem: we've conquered darkness,

270
0:12:45.47,000 --> 0:12:48,000
but in the process, we spill so much extra light out into the night

271
0:12:48.964,000 --> 0:12:51,000
that it disrupts the lives of other creatures,

272
0:12:52.09,000 --> 0:12:55,000
and fireflies are especially sensitive to light pollution

273
0:12:55.534,000 --> 0:12:57,000
because it obscures the signals

274
0:12:58.155,000 --> 0:13:02,000
that they use to find their mates.

275
0:13:02.614,000 --> 0:13:03,000
Do we really need fireflies?

276
0:13:04.592,000 --> 0:13:06,000
After all, they're just one tiny bit

277
0:13:06.631,000 --> 0:13:08,000
of Earth's biodiversity.

278
0:13:08.9,000 --> 0:13:11,000
Yet every time a species is lost,

279
0:13:12.208,000 --> 0:13:14,000
it's like extinguishing a room full of candles

280
0:13:14.897,000 --> 0:13:16,000
one by one.

281
0:13:17.825,000 --> 0:13:17,000
You might not notice

282
0:13:18.771,000 --> 0:13:21,000
when the first few flames flicker out,

283
0:13:22.061,000 --> 0:13:26,000
but in the end, you're left sitting in darkness.

284
0:13:31.591,000 --> 0:13:35,000
As we work together to craft a planetary future,

285
0:13:36.411,000 --> 0:13:38,000
I hope we can find a way

286
0:13:38.875,000 --> 0:13:41,000
to keep these bright lights shining.

287
0:13:42.328,000 --> 0:13:44,000
Thank you.

288
0:13:44.364,000 --> 0:13:46,000
